  "prompt": "How do I apply for improvement in the 12th CBSE exam?",
  "response": "To apply for improvement in the 12th CBSE (Central Board of Secondary Education) exam, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Check Eligibility:**\n   Ensure that you have passed your 12th CBSE examination and are looking to improve your scores in one or more subjects. Students can apply for improvement in one or more subjects in the succeeding year only after the year they have appeared for the board exams.\n\n2. **Visit the CBSE Website:**\n   Go to the official CBSE website (www.cbse.nic.in).\n\n3. **Locate the Improvement Exam Form:**\n   Look for the section related to the improvement exam. This is generally found in the 'Examinations' or 'Forms' section of the website.\n\n4. **Online Registration:**\n   Fill in the required details in the online application form. You will need to provide personal details, previous roll number, subject details, etc.\n\n5. **Upload Documents:**\n   Upload necessary documents, such as a photograph and the mark sheet of the 12th standard.\n\n6. **Pay the Fee:**\n   Pay the examination fee online. The fee varies based on the number of subjects you are applying for. Payment methods might include credit/debit card or other online payment options.\n\n7. **Submit the Form:**\n   After completing the above steps, submit the online form. Make sure to double-check all information before submission.\n\n8. **Print Confirmation:**\n   After successful submission, take a printout of the confirmation page for your records. \n\nKeep an eye on the CBSE website for any announcements regarding the improvement exam schedule and admit cards. \n\nAfter applying, make sure to prepare well for your selected subjects, as the improvement exam is an opportunity to better your scores.\n\nAlways keep track of deadlines and updates provided by CBSE to ensure a smooth application process.",
